verbose_text: When NE binds to the active site of AAT, the Met358-Ser359 bond, cleavage of this Met Ser bond results in the generation of a tight, non covalent interaction between NE and AAT thereby inhibiting NE activity and causing release of the 36-amino acid C-terminal Ser359-Lys394 peptide [XREF_BIBR].
